HEADWORD: Jaconet
<hw>Jac"o*net</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>jaconas</ets>.]</ety> <def>A thin cotton fabric, between cambric
and muslin, used for dresses, neckcloths, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>jacconet</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

